      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/f1717-controlled-experiment-req-001",
      "type": "Requirement",
      "name": "Controlled-experiment verification requirement for F1717 compression-bending FEA",
      "description": "Per the project verification plan (VP-FEA-2024-003), the FEA model for ASTM F1717 compression-bending shall be validated by means of a controlled experiment in which loading conditions, specimen geometry, and boundary conditions are prospectively specified and independently replicated across at least two laboratories. This requirement is classified as a primary credibility-substantiation requirement under ASME V&V 40 Section 6.",
      "requiredVerificationMethod": "controlled-experiment"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/f1717-bench-data-collection-obs-001",
      "type": "Activity",
      "name": "Retrospective bench-data collation for F1717 compression-bending comparison",
      "description": "Bench test data for N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were collated from two independent laboratory archives (FDA CDRH biomechanics laboratory and DePuy Synthes internal testing). Data collection followed each laboratory's standard operating procedures; no prospective protocol was issued by the modeling team prior to testing. Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement were extracted from archived load-displacement curves and provided to the FEA team for comparison. The two laboratories operated under identical ASTM F1717 test standard conditions, and results were found to be mutually consistent, lending high confidence to the comparison.",
      "activityType": "observational-study",
      "startedAtTime": "2023-06-01T00:00:00Z",
      "endedAtTime": "2023-11-30T00:00:00Z",
      "wasAssociatedWith": "https://uofa.net/synth/org/nagaraja-fda-depaul-team"
    }
  ],
